market_context: European markets closed mixed. US 10-year yield holding at 4.54%. Retail sector showing weakness after Home Depot guidance disappointed. AI spending narrative supporting large-cap tech.

predictions.reasoning: QQQ found support at the 20-day moving average overnight. AI capex announcements from Microsoft and Meta this week reaffirm tech spend thesis. Expect modest recovery.

Google Cloud momentum and Gemini model traction supporting multiple expansion. Advertising revenue resilience in macro uncertainty. Technical breakout above 185 resistance confirms trend.
Intraday dip likely to be bought. Institutional flows remain positive. The 600 level has been defended four times in February. No major macro catalyst to break the range today.
